urls.title: Elon Musk Reportedly Considers a Second Twitter HQ in Texas
urls.description: Per Fox and The Verge Elon Musk said there are "no plans" to move Twitter's headquarters to Texas like Tesla. However, he said it made sense for the company to be dual-headquartered in California and Texas. Texas governor Greg Abbott reacted to the news on Twitter with eyeball emojis. Musk moved Tesla's headquarters to Austin, Texas, in Dec 2021 from Palo Alto, California. SpaceX also has a launch site in South Texas with plans to build a testing facility near Waco.
